    <note type="biography">
        <p>German geographer. Studied law and history at Heidelberg and Leipzig, 1845–8. Editor, <hi rend="italic">Augsburger Allgemeine Zeitung</hi>, 1850. Chief editor at J. G. Cotta’schen Buchhandlung in Augsburg, 1854. Director of the weekly geographical newspaper <hi rend="italic">Das Ausland</hi>, 1854. First chair of the geography department, University of Leipzig, 1871. Introduced Darwinian concepts of change and distribution as analytical tools in geography.</p></note>
